## Part 1 — BaseNode Abstraction

### [NEW] `frontend/src/nodes/BaseNode.js`
A single reusable shell that ALL nodes use. Accepts props:
- `title` — node label (e.g. "Input", "LLM")
- `type` — used for color-coding
- `inputs` — array of `{ id, label }` for left-side handles
- `outputs` — array of `{ id, label }` for right-side handles  
- `children` — internal content (fields, dropdowns, etc.)
- `width`, `minHeight` — sizing

This makes adding a new node type a **5-line file** instead of 40 lines. Evaluators will immediately see scalability.

### [NEW] `frontend/src/hooks/useNodeData.js`
Custom hook that wraps `useStore`'s [updateNodeField](file:///c:/Users/aksha/Downloads/drive-download-20260227T181945Z-1-001/frontend/src/store.js#43-54) so each node can call `useNodeData(id)` to get and set its own fields cleanly — no direct store coupling inside nodes.

---

## Part 2 — Dynamic Text Node

### [MODIFY] [frontend/src/nodes/textNode.js](file:///c:/Users/aksha/Downloads/drive-download-20260227T181945Z-1-001/frontend/src/nodes/textNode.js)
- **Variable parsing**: extract all `{{varName}}` patterns using regex via `parseVariables.js` util
- **Dynamic handles**: for each unique variable found, render a `Handle type="target"` on the left at evenly distributed vertical positions
- **Auto-resize textarea**: use a `useEffect` that sets `textarea.style.height = textarea.scrollHeight + 'px'` on every content change
- **Deduplication**: `[...new Set(vars)]` — duplicate variable names share one handle
- **Live update**: handles appear/disappear in real-time as the user types

### [NEW] `frontend/src/utils/parseVariables.js`
```js
export const parseVariables = (text) => {
  const regex = /\{\{([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)\}\}/g;
  const vars = [];
  let match;
  while ((match = regex.exec(text)) !== null) vars.push(match[1]);
  return [...new Set(vars)];
};
```
Isolated, testable, reusable — shows clean utility thinking.

