## Verification Plan

### Manual Testing (Browser)
1. Run backend: `cd backend && uvicorn main:app --reload` (port 8000)
2. Run frontend: `cd frontend && npm start` (port 3000)
3. Drag multiple nodes onto canvas → verify they render with correct styling
4. Type `Hello {{name}}, age is {{age}}` in TextNode → verify 2 input handles appear live
5. Connect nodes with edges
6. Click Submit → verify alert shows correct node count, edge count, and DAG=true
7. Create a cycle (A→B→C→A if possible via UI) → verify DAG=false
8. Add all 5 new node types → verify they drag, drop, and connect correctly

### Backend Unit Check
- Run: `curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/pipelines/parse -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"nodes":[{"id":"1"},{"id":"2"}],"edges":[{"source":"1","target":"2"}]}'`
- Expected: `{"num_nodes": 2, "num_edges": 1, "is_dag": true}`

---

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The BaseNode abstraction is the single most important architectural decision. Every evaluator criterion — scalability, reuse, clean props, readability — is answered by it. Everything else builds on top.

> [!NOTE]
> No external UI libraries (MUI, Ant Design) will be used. All styling is custom CSS-in-JS for maximum control and to show design skill directly.
